### BUG-02: `VITE_BACKEND_URL` vs `REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL` Env Mismatch
**Problem:** `api.js` and `AuthContext.jsx` read `import.meta.env?.VITE_BACKEND_URL || process.env.REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL`. With Vite, only `VITE_` prefixed env vars are exposed. With CRA, only `REACT_APP_` vars. The `?.` optional chaining on `import.meta.env` hides the bug silently.

**Fix — Standardise on Vite:**
```js
// src/utils/api.js
const BASE_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_BACKEND_URL || 'http://localhost:5001';
```

Create `careerforge-pro/.env.example`:
```env
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:5001
```

Create `careerforge-pro/.env.production`:
```env
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your-backend.railway.app
```

